comments.en: Its objective is to model and represent the structure, relationships and concepts related to flight satisfaction surveys

comment.en: Representing a trip undertaken for leisure or recreational purposes
Represents an airport location where flights depart from or arrive at. Airports serve as essential nodes in the transportation network, facilitating air travel for passengers and cargo.
Represents a geographic location or place
Representing a vehicle that is capable of flight through the atmosphere
Representing a business class seat on a flight

A subtype of the general class "Passenger", specifically denoting individuals who hold Canadian nationality. Canadian passengers are individuals from Canada who engage in air travel for various purposes such as business, leisure, or family visits.

A subtype of Review, representing feedback that emphasizes positive aspects of the travel experience. Good reviews may commend excellent service, comfortable seating, or timely arrivals, serving as testimonials of satisfaction
Generally refers to a sovereign geographical and political entity, with its own borders, government and citizenship.
Represent a person traveling in a vehicle (car, plane, train) or on foot.
Representing a survey designed to measure satisfaction levels of individuals after a specific experience, such as a flight
Representing a seat on a flight
Representing a premium economy class seat on a flight
Representing a company that provides air transport services for passengers or freight
A subtype of Passenger, representing individuals with Spanish nationality. Spanish passengers are citizens of Spain who travel by air, reflecting the diverse range of travelers from Spain.
Representing a leisure trip undertaken by a family
Representing a first class seat on a flight
Representing a Economy class seat on a flight
Representing the act of moving from one place to another, typically over a distance
Representing a trip undertaken for business purposes

A general class encompassing all individuals who engage in travel activities, including air travel. Travelers can be of any nationality and may embark on journeys for various reasons, such as tourism, business, or personal commitments
Defines a route taken by an aircraft, typically between two airports. Flight routes play a crucial role in flight planning and scheduling, determining the path an aircraft follows during its journey.
Representing a leisure trip undertaken by a couple

A subtype of the general class "Passenger", specifically denoting individuals who hold German nationality. German passengers are citizens of Germany who travel by air, contributing to international air traffic.
Representing a leisure trip undertaken by a individual alone

A subtype of Review, specifically indicating feedback that highlights negative aspects of the travel experience. Negative reviews may include complaints about flight delays, poor service, or discomfort, providing insights into areas for improvement.

Represents a feedback or evaluation provided by a traveler regarding their travel experience. Reviews typically include information about the flight, airline, service quality, and overall satisfaction, helping other travelers make informed decisions.
Indicates the aircraft used for a specific trip.
Indicates the passenger who completed the survey
Indicates the arrival airport for a flight route.
Denotes the date when the trip or journey took place or was undertaken.
Indicates the main content or body of the review or opinion.
Indicates that an entity contains an airport.
Indicates the country associated with an entity.
Indicates that a passenger takes part in a trip.
Indicates the departure airport for a flight route.
Indicates the aircraft operated by an airline.
Indicates that an entity is owned by another.
Indicates the flight seat associated with a trip.
Represents the feedback or commentary provided regarding a trip
Indicates that a passenger provides a review.
Indicates the airport(s) located in a country.
Indicates the flight route followed during a trip.
Denotes the title or headline of the review or opinion.
Indicates the trip reason associated with a trip.
Indicates that an entity is located in another place.
Indicates the country of origin of a passenger.
Indicates that an airport serves the operations of an airline.
Indicates the airport(s) from which an airline operates.
Indicates whether the review or opinion has been verified or authenticated.
Specifies whether the subject of the review or opinion is recommended or not.
Indicates the location of an airport or country.
Quantifies the evaluation or score given to the subject of the review or opinion.
Indicates the country associated with an entity.
Indicates the passenger(s) associated with a trip.
Represents the date when the review or opinion was published.
Indicates that a trip reason is the reason for a trip.
